subSubSection.paragraph:
Rostral border of cranium broad with mesethmoid broader than longer, premaxilla underneath with synchondral articulation; cranial fontanel elliptical, with single large opening, bounded by mesethmoid and frontal; nasal ossified, tubular, with no medial flanges (
Fig. 17
). Autopalatine tubular, oriented obliquely to longitudinal axis of body; maxilla about same size of autopalatine; prevomer expanded with a well developed arrow-shaped lateral processes; jaws of equal size; premaxilla and dentary with three rows of conical teeth. First nuchal plate short, pentagonal; second nuchal plate laterally concave; third nuchal plate projected laterally, with pronounced narrow tip. Epioccipital process small.
